  "text": "To data, large number of techniques have been proposed to handle data skew in join executions [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] . Among them, we have chosen a very efficient method, partial duplication [CITATION_5] , in our implementations. Its core idea is: large number of skewed tuples in an input relation are kept locally and not transferred at all, instead, just a very small number of non-skewed tuples from another relation are broadcast to all other nodes. Within such a scheme, the constraints in our optimization model (1) is extended as:",
